						<p class="author">
									<a class="unread" href="./viewtopic.php?p=1473#p1473" title="Post">
						<i class="icon fa-file fa-fw icon-lightgray icon-md" aria-hidden="true"></i><span class="sr-only">Post</span>
					</a>
								<span class="responsive-hide">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1588" class="username">GrailerDiomede</a></strong> &raquo; </span><time datetime="2020-03-20T23:40:10+00:00">Fri Mar 20, 2020 11:40 pm</time>
			</p>
			
			
			
			<div class="content">The build guide for your Rotary Cell Phone design seems to be far beyond my physical skill set (very limited soldering experience and not much else) and knowledge.  <br>
<br>
Aside from finding a local mentor or group, do you have any recommendations on resources to help build the proper physical skills and knowledge needed to follow along with a build like this?  Given the current nCOVID-19 imposed restrictions, attempted self-teaching is the only available path on the long road to being able to approach something like this.<br>
<br>
If not, no worries; this tastes like a design for experienced people.<br>
<br>
Thank you for sharing your work.</div>

			
			
									
									
