		<div class="postbody">
						<div id="post_content1493">

						<h3 ><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=1493#p1493">Re: Learning Resources</a></h3>

													<ul class="post-buttons">
																																									<li>
							<a href="./posting.php?mode=quote&amp;f=4&amp;p=1493" title="Reply with quote" class="button button-icon-only">
								<i class="icon fa-quote-left fa-fw" aria-hidden="true"></i><span class="sr-only">Quote</span>
							</a>
						</li>
														</ul>
							
						<p class="author">
									<a class="unread" href="./viewtopic.php?p=1493#p1493" title="Post">
						<i class="icon fa-file fa-fw icon-lightgray icon-md" aria-hidden="true"></i><span class="sr-only">Post</span>
					</a>
								<span class="responsive-hide">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1745" class="username">nemomtt</a></strong> &raquo; </span><time datetime="2020-04-07T18:09:05+00:00">Tue Apr 07, 2020 6:09 pm</time>
			</p>
			
			
			
			<div class="content">Hi Grailer,<br>
<br>
As with all skills, practice is key.  When the world comes back to something resembling normal you could check for a maker faire in your area, they often have learn to solder workshops.  My son started going those workshops when he was around 10 and it continues to be one of his highlights of the faire.  He is so in love with the workshops he talked me into teaching one on foam carving to make tombstones for Halloween.  It was a lot of fun as he was my assent teacher.<br>
<br>
Amazon has many learn to solder kits.  Take your time and remember no one got it right the first time.  When mastering new skills the three most important things to remember are practice, practice and practice. <br>
<br>
When it comes to making a complex project, experience with any handcraft can help you develop transferable hand control skills.  When I was young I enjoyed making plastic model kits. I learned a lot of skills this way, partially patience and thinking the problem through. So, while you are cooped up I would order the handcraft kits of your choice and just keep working at it. This might also help your overall sanity.</div>

			
			
									
									
						</div>

		</div>

